WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.920 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.920 --> 00:00:17.180 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.180 --> 00:00:20.120 align:middle line:84%
Hi, I'm Lisa Garr, host
of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:22.600 align:middle line:84%
We're coming to you live
from the Gaiam studios

00:00:22.600 --> 00:00:23.880 align:middle line:90%
in Boulder, Colorado.

00:00:23.880 --> 00:00:25.630 align:middle line:10%
And since it's a live
interactive show,

00:00:25.630 --> 00:00:27.450 align:middle line:10%
I encourage you to
communicate with us

00:00:27.450 --> 00:00:28.990 align:middle line:10%
through Facebook and Twitter.

00:00:28.990 --> 00:00:30.130 align:middle line:10%
Many of you already are.

00:00:30.130 --> 00:00:31.580 align:middle line:10%
So keep the comments
and questions

00:00:31.580 --> 00:00:33.210 align:middle line:10%
coming throughout the show.

00:00:33.210 --> 00:00:35.030 align:middle line:10%
According to my guests
today, visionary

00:00:35.030 --> 00:00:37.480 align:middle line:10%
futurist Barbara Marx
Hubbard, we're facing

00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:39.190 align:middle line:10%
a historic turning point.

00:00:39.190 --> 00:00:42.070 align:middle line:84%
We're evolving from
an unconscious chance

00:00:42.070 --> 00:00:43.830 align:middle line:90%
to conscious choice.

00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:46.110 align:middle line:84%
We're entering into what
Barbara calls the First

00:00:46.110 --> 00:00:48.440 align:middle line:90%
Age of Conscious Evolution.

00:00:48.440 --> 00:00:50.360 align:middle line:84%
However, in order for
something new to start,

00:00:50.360 --> 00:00:53.380 align:middle line:84%
quite often something
old needs to fall apart.

00:00:53.380 --> 00:00:56.135 align:middle line:84%
And this is something many
people are experiencing today.

00:00:56.135 --> 00:00:59.110 align:middle line:84%
And one of the greatest ways
to move through this shift

00:00:59.110 --> 00:01:02.510 align:middle line:84%
is to start a new conversation,
to move humanity from one

00:01:02.510 --> 00:01:04.910 align:middle line:90%
phase of evolution to the next.

00:01:04.910 --> 00:01:07.620 align:middle line:84%
Barbara has authored
seven acclaimed books

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:11.320 align:middle line:84%
that communicate a new world
view of conscious evolution.

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:13.840 align:middle line:84%
And she's joining us
here today to share

00:01:13.840 --> 00:01:15.620 align:middle line:90%
her massive inspiration.

00:01:15.620 --> 00:01:16.790 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, to the show.

00:01:16.790 --> 00:01:17.670 align:middle line:90%
Thank you, Lisa.

00:01:17.670 --> 00:01:19.390 align:middle line:90%
I'm really happy to be he.

00:01:19.390 --> 00:01:20.630 align:middle line:90%
It is our true honor.

00:01:20.630 --> 00:01:22.730 align:middle line:84%
And I am so grateful
that you're here.

00:01:22.730 --> 00:01:25.750 align:middle line:84%
So talk to us about this
critical tipping point.

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:29.370 align:middle line:84%
You talk about facing either
extinction or evolution.

00:01:29.370 --> 00:01:30.560 align:middle line:90%
What do you mean by that?

00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:33.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's obvious we
can't keep over growing

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:34.810 align:middle line:90%
in a finite planet.

00:01:34.810 --> 00:01:39.320 align:middle line:10%
And our crisis is literally
an evolutionary driver

00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:42.910 align:middle line:10%
toward either destruction
of our environment

00:01:42.910 --> 00:01:46.150 align:middle line:10%
or an evolution of our species.

00:01:46.150 --> 00:01:50.430 align:middle line:10%
And I believe conscious
evolution is becoming conscious

00:01:50.430 --> 00:01:52.980 align:middle line:10%
that we can affect
our own future

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:56.090 align:middle line:10%
and then acting by
choice positively.

00:01:56.090 --> 00:01:58.260 align:middle line:84%
So conscious evolution,
what specifically

00:01:58.260 --> 00:02:00.770 align:middle line:84%
is-- break that down for
me, conscious evolution.

00:02:00.770 --> 00:02:03.080 align:middle line:90%
We are aware of evolution.

00:02:03.080 --> 00:02:05.750 align:middle line:84%
We can look back and see
billions of years that it took.

00:02:05.750 --> 00:02:06.900 align:middle line:90%
We are aware.

00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:10.050 align:middle line:84%
We are affecting our own
evolution by everything we do,

00:02:10.050 --> 00:02:13.310 align:middle line:84%
the babies we have, the food
we eat, the cars we drive.

00:02:13.310 --> 00:02:15.840 align:middle line:84%
We're also aware
that our behavior

00:02:15.840 --> 00:02:20.050 align:middle line:84%
could destroy our civilization
and our environment.

00:02:20.050 --> 00:02:24.880 align:middle line:84%
So conscious evolution is
saying I'm willing to be aware

00:02:24.880 --> 00:02:28.210 align:middle line:84%
that this is a design
that I could help create,

00:02:28.210 --> 00:02:31.940 align:middle line:84%
that my thoughts, my
actions, my choices

00:02:31.940 --> 00:02:34.610 align:middle line:84%
are going to make the
difference for this world.

00:02:34.610 --> 00:02:35.700 align:middle line:90%
Which they are.

00:02:35.700 --> 00:02:38.170 align:middle line:84%
Now, you started
off as a homemaker.

00:02:38.170 --> 00:02:41.690 align:middle line:84%
And you're now a
visionary futurist.

00:02:41.690 --> 00:02:43.520 align:middle line:90%
What was your journey like?

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:46.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, it really
started for me in 1945

00:02:46.590 --> 00:02:49.800 align:middle line:84%
when the United States dropped
the first bombs on Japan.

00:02:49.800 --> 00:02:52.780 align:middle line:90%
I was 15 years old in 1945.

00:02:52.780 --> 00:02:56.080 align:middle line:84%
And I always thought everything
was going for the good.

00:02:56.080 --> 00:02:59.890 align:middle line:84%
But suddenly, I saw that we
could misuse that great power

00:02:59.890 --> 00:03:01.860 align:middle line:90%
and destroy our species.

00:03:01.860 --> 00:03:04.650 align:middle line:84%
So I asked a question,
what's the meaning

00:03:04.650 --> 00:03:07.930 align:middle line:84%
of the new power--
science, technology,

00:03:07.930 --> 00:03:09.840 align:middle line:90%
industry-- that's good?

00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:13.910 align:middle line:84%
Were you raised with a kind
of an idealistic point of view?

00:03:13.910 --> 00:03:15.900 align:middle line:90%
No, my father was a toymaker.

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:20.910 align:middle line:84%
It was materialistic, secular,
competitive New York business.

00:03:20.910 --> 00:03:22.280 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Interesting,
interesting.

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:25.470 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD: How
he got me, I don't know.

00:03:25.470 --> 00:03:28.180 align:middle line:84%
Well you arose
from that lifestyle,

00:03:28.180 --> 00:03:31.660 align:middle line:84%
from that upbringing,
to being someone

00:03:31.660 --> 00:03:35.690 align:middle line:84%
who holds answer questions,
very, very strong questions.

00:03:35.690 --> 00:03:37.670 align:middle line:90%
And you follow them through.

00:03:37.670 --> 00:03:39.190 align:middle line:84%
You had an incident
where you, I guess,

00:03:39.190 --> 00:03:41.760 align:middle line:84%
you wound up in the Oval Office
because of your father, right?

00:03:41.760 --> 00:03:42.560 align:middle line:90%
Well, I did.

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:44.430 align:middle line:84%
And it was that
sense of hope that I

00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:47.210 align:middle line:84%
got from that
entrepreneurial spirit.

00:03:47.210 --> 00:03:52.060 align:middle line:84%
And my father once gave
a toy train to a general

00:03:52.060 --> 00:03:55.010 align:middle line:84%
in the Air Force, got to
know all the generals.

00:03:55.010 --> 00:03:58.000 align:middle line:84%
And they became godfathers
of my half brothers.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:02.910 align:middle line:84%
So one day in 1952, I was
invited to the Oval Office

00:04:02.910 --> 00:04:05.407 align:middle line:84%
just to say hello to
President Eisenhower.

00:04:05.407 --> 00:04:06.640 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Oh, my
goodness, you found

00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:08.620 align:middle line:84%
yourself with a lot
of different generals

00:04:08.620 --> 00:04:11.654 align:middle line:90%
and in an incredible place.

00:04:11.654 --> 00:04:13.020 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD:
So Eisenhower would

00:04:13.020 --> 00:04:14.510 align:middle line:90%
just say, hello, young lady.

00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:15.270 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:04:15.270 --> 00:04:17.350 align:middle line:90%
It was a courtesy call.

00:04:17.350 --> 00:04:20.750 align:middle line:84%
So I said, Mr. President,
I have a question for you.

00:04:20.750 --> 00:04:22.790 align:middle line:90%
Yes, what is it?

00:04:22.790 --> 00:04:25.950 align:middle line:84%
What do you think is the
meaning of our new power

00:04:25.950 --> 00:04:29.620 align:middle line:84%
of science, technology, industry
in the military that's good?

00:04:29.620 --> 00:04:30.810 align:middle line:90%
You asked him that?

00:04:30.810 --> 00:04:34.110 align:middle line:84%
And he stared at me and
shook his head and he said,

00:04:34.110 --> 00:04:36.420 align:middle line:90%
I have no idea.

00:04:36.420 --> 00:04:39.500 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well,
we better find out.

00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:41.760 align:middle line:84%
So you have the
president at the time

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:44.590 align:middle line:84%
what is the meaning of
all of our new power

00:04:44.590 --> 00:04:45.490 align:middle line:90%
and he didn't know.

00:04:45.490 --> 00:04:46.723 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD:
He had no idea.

00:04:46.723 --> 00:04:47.900 align:middle line:90%
He hadn't thought of it.

00:04:47.900 --> 00:04:51.290 align:middle line:84%
And as I started to research,
science, and philosophy,

00:04:51.290 --> 00:04:53.840 align:middle line:84%
and religion, and
academic world,

00:04:53.840 --> 00:04:57.560 align:middle line:84%
I found we did not have
any vision of our future

00:04:57.560 --> 00:05:01.320 align:middle line:84%
that we want to work
toward equal to our power

00:05:01.320 --> 00:05:03.330 align:middle line:90%
to destroy or create.

00:05:03.330 --> 00:05:05.301 align:middle line:84%
So you started to follow
this question through it,

00:05:05.301 --> 00:05:06.455 align:middle line:84%
didn't you?
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD: I did.

00:05:06.455 --> 00:05:07.670 align:middle line:90%
And where did that lead you?

00:05:07.670 --> 00:05:10.010 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD:
Well, it lead me right here

00:05:10.010 --> 00:05:13.500 align:middle line:84%
to the awareness that
the crisis we're facing

00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:16.440 align:middle line:84%
is potentially the
birth of what I'm

00:05:16.440 --> 00:05:19.680 align:middle line:90%
calling a co-creative humanity.

00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:24.010 align:middle line:84%
It would be a humanity in which
each person is free to express

00:05:24.010 --> 00:05:27.440 align:middle line:84%
that creativity, to give their
gift to the larger world,

00:05:27.440 --> 00:05:29.810 align:middle line:84%
to realize potential,
and to connect

00:05:29.810 --> 00:05:31.330 align:middle line:90%
to create a better world.

00:05:31.330 --> 00:05:33.590 align:middle line:90%
That's the meaning of our power.

00:05:33.590 --> 00:05:36.500 align:middle line:84%
And so then you wound
up going to NASA.

00:05:36.500 --> 00:05:39.080 align:middle line:84%
You wound up going
to different places.

00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:42.120 align:middle line:84%
Your theme, your through line
has been this exact same thing

00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:45.390 align:middle line:84%
to really affect
evolution, to make

00:05:45.390 --> 00:05:48.040 align:middle line:84%
a huge difference with our
conversation, isn't it?

00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:50.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, when I started
to ask these questions

00:05:50.490 --> 00:05:54.180 align:middle line:84%
there was no discipline, no
field, no subject at Bryn

00:05:54.180 --> 00:05:55.710 align:middle line:90%
Mawr College, where I went.

00:05:55.710 --> 00:05:59.220 align:middle line:84%
So eventually I became
what's called a futurist.

00:05:59.220 --> 00:06:00.660 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: What did
you study in college?

00:06:00.660 --> 00:06:02.960 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD: I
studied political science

00:06:02.960 --> 00:06:06.250 align:middle line:84%
because I didn't know what
my deeper purpose was.

00:06:06.250 --> 00:06:07.750 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: But you
learned the current story.

00:06:07.750 --> 00:06:08.449 align:middle line:90%
You learned--

00:06:08.449 --> 00:06:10.420 align:middle line:84%
I learned a lot about
the current story.

00:06:10.420 --> 00:06:12.640 align:middle line:90%
I went to Paris my junior year.

00:06:12.640 --> 00:06:16.150 align:middle line:84%
I met my husband in a little
cafe on the left bank.

00:06:16.150 --> 00:06:18.480 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him my
question, what's

00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:20.180 align:middle line:90%
the meaning of our new power?

00:06:20.180 --> 00:06:21.680 align:middle line:90%
What do you think it is?

00:06:21.680 --> 00:06:23.910 align:middle line:90%
And he said, I'm an artist.

00:06:23.910 --> 00:06:27.160 align:middle line:84%
And I'm seeking a new
story, a new image

00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:29.040 align:middle line:90%
commensurate with our power.

00:06:29.040 --> 00:06:31.980 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I'm
going to marry you.

00:06:31.980 --> 00:06:32.710 align:middle line:90%
And I did.

00:06:32.710 --> 00:06:33.610 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: And you did.

00:06:33.610 --> 00:06:37.510 align:middle line:84%
I got married on the quest
for what is the story,

00:06:37.510 --> 00:06:41.000 align:middle line:84%
what is the direction, and
how are we going to find it?

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:44.460 align:middle line:84%
And I realized in a way,
it's an art form because it's

00:06:44.460 --> 00:06:45.750 align:middle line:90%
not written down somewhere.

00:06:45.750 --> 00:06:47.520 align:middle line:90%
We have to seek it out.

00:06:47.520 --> 00:06:49.050 align:middle line:84%
So when I asked you
the question of how

00:06:49.050 --> 00:06:51.530 align:middle line:84%
did you go from being a
homemaker to a futurist,

00:06:51.530 --> 00:06:53.810 align:middle line:90%
you always have been a futurist.

00:06:53.810 --> 00:06:55.330 align:middle line:90%
I got married.

00:06:55.330 --> 00:06:56.560 align:middle line:90%
And my husband was an artist.

00:06:56.560 --> 00:06:58.780 align:middle line:84%
And Of course, I
had five children.

00:06:58.780 --> 00:07:00.620 align:middle line:90%
In the meantime, that happened.

00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:06.530 align:middle line:84%
From the 1951 to about
1970, I was a full-time mom.

00:07:06.530 --> 00:07:08.930 align:middle line:90%
And I sort of lost the question.

00:07:08.930 --> 00:07:10.700 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: You were
doing something else.

00:07:10.700 --> 00:07:12.480 align:middle line:90%
I was having babies.

00:07:12.480 --> 00:07:16.670 align:middle line:84%
And every baby was yet
another wonderful being.

00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:19.690 align:middle line:84%
So the question would
deepen with each child,

00:07:19.690 --> 00:07:21.720 align:middle line:84%
because if you didn't
know the direction

00:07:21.720 --> 00:07:24.580 align:middle line:84%
of the future for
yourself, how could you

00:07:24.580 --> 00:07:26.830 align:middle line:90%
really educate your children?

00:07:26.830 --> 00:07:28.760 align:middle line:84%
And that was before
we really got

00:07:28.760 --> 00:07:31.030 align:middle line:84%
this sense that the
future was negative

00:07:31.030 --> 00:07:33.260 align:middle line:90%
and might be very much worse.

00:07:33.260 --> 00:07:37.150 align:middle line:84%
But even then, I could see
I wanted my children to know

00:07:37.150 --> 00:07:40.340 align:middle line:84%
that there was something for
them to do that was important,

00:07:40.340 --> 00:07:41.270 align:middle line:90%
that was great.

00:07:41.270 --> 00:07:43.450 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely, so as you
were raising your children,

00:07:43.450 --> 00:07:45.941 align:middle line:84%
you continued this conversation
going throughout your child

00:07:45.941 --> 00:07:47.550 align:middle line:84%
rearing years.
-I did.

00:07:47.550 --> 00:07:50.060 align:middle line:84%
And when I realized
that I had, let's

00:07:50.060 --> 00:07:52.430 align:middle line:84%
say, a calling, a
vocation to tell

00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:54.790 align:middle line:90%
the story of this larger birth.

00:07:54.790 --> 00:07:57.740 align:middle line:84%
When I told my children
that their mom had

00:07:57.740 --> 00:08:00.880 align:middle line:84%
to go tell this story
of the positive future,

00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:04.500 align:middle line:84%
my nine-year-old
son said to me, mom,

00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:07.030 align:middle line:84%
you're doing what
mothers should.

00:08:07.030 --> 00:08:08.600 align:middle line:84%
You're helping to
create a better

00:08:08.600 --> 00:08:10.020 align:middle line:90%
future for your children.

00:08:10.020 --> 00:08:11.040 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: Oh, my goodness.

00:08:11.040 --> 00:08:14.920 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD: And
I know that you love us.

00:08:14.920 --> 00:08:18.980 align:middle line:84%
So I was a mom that
shifted from full-time mom

00:08:18.980 --> 00:08:22.310 align:middle line:84%
to what I would call
evolutionary woman.

00:08:22.310 --> 00:08:24.440 align:middle line:84%
But I brought all
my children with me.

00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:27.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's one reason I love
the nine-year-old so much,

00:08:27.410 --> 00:08:31.220 align:middle line:84%
because my nine-year-old
son, in a way,

00:08:31.220 --> 00:08:33.214 align:middle line:84%
made me realize it was
good for the children.

00:08:33.214 --> 00:08:35.280 align:middle line:84%
See, this is a great question,
because it's actually lighting

00:08:35.280 --> 00:08:38.419 align:middle line:84%
up-- people on Facebook,
they're saying,

00:08:38.419 --> 00:08:40.890 align:middle line:84%
from running from
doing paying the bills

00:08:40.890 --> 00:08:43.150 align:middle line:84%
and going to the soccer games,
how do I get my children

00:08:43.150 --> 00:08:44.730 align:middle line:90%
in this conversation?

00:08:44.730 --> 00:08:46.230 align:middle line:90%
Enrolled in this conversation?

00:08:46.230 --> 00:08:47.590 align:middle line:84%
And that's exactly
how you do it.

00:08:47.590 --> 00:08:48.690 align:middle line:90%
It's all the same thing.

00:08:48.690 --> 00:08:49.430 align:middle line:90%
It's not separate.

00:08:49.430 --> 00:08:50.340 align:middle line:90%
That's the bottom line.

00:08:50.340 --> 00:08:53.450 align:middle line:84%
The children innately
have a sense of the future

00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:57.960 align:middle line:84%
now much more than in the
'70s, because obviously

00:08:57.960 --> 00:08:59.110 align:middle line:90%
they're watching TV.

00:08:59.110 --> 00:09:00.511 align:middle line:90%
They're on their iPads.

00:09:00.511 --> 00:09:01.910 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: Much more
connected, of course.

00:09:01.910 --> 00:09:04.860 align:middle line:84%
Those children at
nine now, many of them

00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:08.310 align:middle line:84%
know more than the older
ones, because they're

00:09:08.310 --> 00:09:09.770 align:middle line:90%
in the new world.

00:09:09.770 --> 00:09:12.780 align:middle line:84%
And they're connected to
the world nervous system,

00:09:12.780 --> 00:09:13.620 align:middle line:90%
which is internet.

00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:15.220 align:middle line:84%
They're connected now.
-Amazing.

00:09:15.220 --> 00:09:17.350 align:middle line:84%
So then you had this
incredible vision.

00:09:17.350 --> 00:09:21.250 align:middle line:84%
You went to go buy a
space shuttle, didn't you?

00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:23.360 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD:
Well, that's not quite--

00:09:23.360 --> 00:09:26.990 align:middle line:84%
what happened was during
the American Apollo program,

00:09:26.990 --> 00:09:31.840 align:middle line:84%
when I saw those rockets go
off, I had this deep sense

00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:34.650 align:middle line:84%
that it was like the fish
coming out of the sea

00:09:34.650 --> 00:09:36.190 align:middle line:90%
onto the dry land.

00:09:36.190 --> 00:09:39.820 align:middle line:84%
Our species was
leaving its biosphere.

00:09:39.820 --> 00:09:42.580 align:middle line:84%
And it was going to
land on a new world.

00:09:42.580 --> 00:09:48.970 align:middle line:84%
And I immediately saw that
our future is going to be new

00:09:48.970 --> 00:09:51.910 align:middle line:84%
and that our new technologies,
like the space program,

00:09:51.910 --> 00:09:54.560 align:middle line:84%
were part of a
species that was going

00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:58.720 align:middle line:84%
to be actually a solar
system species and eventually

00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:00.600 align:middle line:90%
a galactic species.

00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:04.930 align:middle line:84%
And I became so
interested in this

00:10:04.930 --> 00:10:10.470 align:middle line:84%
that I founded the Committee
for the Future in Washington DC.

00:10:10.470 --> 00:10:14.780 align:middle line:84%
And I started to bring together
futurists from every field,

00:10:14.780 --> 00:10:17.750 align:middle line:84%
from health, from education,
from economics, to say

00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:19.231 align:middle line:90%
what is the positive future.

00:10:19.231 --> 00:10:20.930 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: At what year
was this that you started--

00:10:20.930 --> 00:10:22.150 align:middle line:90%
1970.

00:10:22.150 --> 00:10:24.390 align:middle line:84%
My goodness, you started
to have these conversations.

00:10:24.390 --> 00:10:29.390 align:middle line:84%
And a filmmaker,
actually, came to us

00:10:29.390 --> 00:10:31.740 align:middle line:84%
when we were just
founding the Future,

00:10:31.740 --> 00:10:33.380 align:middle line:90%
the Committee for the Future.

00:10:33.380 --> 00:10:35.460 align:middle line:84%
And he said, why
don't you sponsor

00:10:35.460 --> 00:10:39.190 align:middle line:84%
a citizen-sponsored
space mission to the moon

00:10:39.190 --> 00:10:42.850 align:middle line:84%
and bring back lunar
materials and involve

00:10:42.850 --> 00:10:47.470 align:middle line:84%
the people of the world
in exploring a new world?

00:10:47.470 --> 00:10:51.250 align:middle line:84%
And it was such a good idea that
the Committee for the Future

00:10:51.250 --> 00:10:52.820 align:middle line:90%
said, all right.

00:10:52.820 --> 00:10:55.880 align:middle line:84%
And we had astronauts
who said yes.

00:10:55.880 --> 00:11:00.620 align:middle line:84%
I went to Cartier and I
said, what would you pay

00:11:00.620 --> 00:11:02.570 align:middle line:90%
for 400 pounds of moon rock?

00:11:02.570 --> 00:11:04.140 align:middle line:90%
They said $400 million.

00:11:04.140 --> 00:11:09.970 align:middle line:84%
So we had enough money to
actually rent a rocket soon.

00:11:09.970 --> 00:11:11.430 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: This is an
unbelievable story.

00:11:11.430 --> 00:11:13.110 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD:
So we went to NASA

00:11:13.110 --> 00:11:15.330 align:middle line:84%
and asked Wernher von
Braun if the people

00:11:15.330 --> 00:11:18.010 align:middle line:90%
could rent a Saturn V rocket.

00:11:18.010 --> 00:11:19.960 align:middle line:90%
And he was totally stunned.

00:11:19.960 --> 00:11:23.300 align:middle line:84%
He said, well, I
don't see why not.

00:11:23.300 --> 00:11:25.860 align:middle line:84%
So he took me into
the place where

00:11:25.860 --> 00:11:31.420 align:middle line:84%
they had these great symbols
of the lift of humanity.

00:11:31.420 --> 00:11:34.160 align:middle line:84%
And I took out my lipstick
and I wrote on one of them,

00:11:34.160 --> 00:11:35.581 align:middle line:90%
"The People's Rocket."

00:11:35.581 --> 00:11:37.054 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my god.

00:11:37.054 --> 00:11:39.890 align:middle line:90%
I wish I had a picture of that.

00:11:39.890 --> 00:11:40.970 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my goodness.

00:11:40.970 --> 00:11:45.170 align:middle line:84%
Eventually NASA wouldn't
let us do it because they

00:11:45.170 --> 00:11:47.150 align:middle line:90%
said it wasn't scientific.

00:11:47.150 --> 00:11:49.650 align:middle line:84%
But actually, we were going
to do a little experiment

00:11:49.650 --> 00:11:51.030 align:middle line:90%
on what would grow on the moon.

00:11:51.030 --> 00:11:53.570 align:middle line:84%
We called it Project
Harvest Moon.

00:11:53.570 --> 00:11:57.550 align:middle line:84%
So with that, I became
truly a pioneering woman.

00:11:57.550 --> 00:11:59.795 align:middle line:84%
Well, absolutely I would
say so in an entrepreneur

00:11:59.795 --> 00:12:02.950 align:middle line:84%
at heart because you were able
to broker this whole deal.

00:12:02.950 --> 00:12:05.980 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD: I'm
known as one of the first space

00:12:05.980 --> 00:12:07.040 align:middle line:90%
entrepreneurs.

00:12:07.040 --> 00:12:09.120 align:middle line:90%
It's too funny.

00:12:09.120 --> 00:12:11.470 align:middle line:84%
Well, I appreciate you
sharing your story with us,

00:12:11.470 --> 00:12:14.800 align:middle line:84%
because these are stories that
make such a big difference.

00:12:14.800 --> 00:12:17.470 align:middle line:84%
And then you wound
up running as a vice

00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:19.957 align:middle line:90%
presidential candidate in 1984.

00:12:19.957 --> 00:12:20.890 align:middle line:90%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD: I did.

00:12:20.890 --> 00:12:24.820 align:middle line:10%
And I want to tell you when
I realized that our story was

00:12:24.820 --> 00:12:28.880 align:middle line:10%
part of the universe story--
I call it a crisis of birth

00:12:28.880 --> 00:12:32.000 align:middle line:10%
of a co-creative,
co-evolving humanity--

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:36.360 align:middle line:10%
everything I did was about
how to tell the bigger story.

00:12:36.360 --> 00:12:40.300 align:middle line:84%
So actually the Saturn
V rocket was in order

00:12:40.300 --> 00:12:43.970 align:middle line:84%
to tell the story that
we're going to be able to be

00:12:43.970 --> 00:12:45.830 align:middle line:90%
a solar system species.

00:12:45.830 --> 00:12:49.530 align:middle line:84%
Running for vice president
was not because I was going

00:12:49.530 --> 00:12:51.380 align:middle line:90%
to be a full time politician.

00:12:51.380 --> 00:12:56.780 align:middle line:84%
But Buckminster Fuller,
he made the geodesic dome.

00:12:56.780 --> 00:13:01.330 align:middle line:84%
He said, space ship Earth came
without an operating manual.

00:13:01.330 --> 00:13:06.550 align:middle line:84%
And he said to me, women
should go into politics to

00:13:06.550 --> 00:13:08.740 align:middle line:90%
present options for the future.

00:13:08.740 --> 00:13:11.900 align:middle line:84%
And Barbara, you should
run for president.

00:13:11.900 --> 00:13:14.660 align:middle line:84%
Oh, so he was the
influence behind this.

00:13:14.660 --> 00:13:18.570 align:middle line:84%
I decided to do what in
America is very typical,

00:13:18.570 --> 00:13:21.030 align:middle line:90%
an idea candidacy.

00:13:21.030 --> 00:13:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And I called it "Campaign
for a Positive Future."

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:27.990 align:middle line:84%
And I had a great idea that the
vice president should create

00:13:27.990 --> 00:13:31.710 align:middle line:84%
a new function to map, track,
and connect, and communicate

00:13:31.710 --> 00:13:33.540 align:middle line:90%
what's working in America.

00:13:33.540 --> 00:13:34.720 align:middle line:90%
LISA GARR: In 1984.

00:13:34.720 --> 00:13:35.750 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:13:35.750 --> 00:13:37.450 align:middle line:90%
I want around the country.

00:13:37.450 --> 00:13:39.480 align:middle line:90%
Positive Future Centers formed.

00:13:39.480 --> 00:13:41.830 align:middle line:84%
I went to the Democratic
National Convention

00:13:41.830 --> 00:13:45.220 align:middle line:84%
with no money, no media,
and no passes to the floor.

00:13:45.220 --> 00:13:50.550 align:middle line:84%
I got into the governor's wife
of Colorado-- interesting.

00:13:50.550 --> 00:13:55.140 align:middle line:84%
And I went to these early
morning caucuses and said,

00:13:55.140 --> 00:13:56.010 align:middle line:90%
I'm Barbara Hubbard.

00:13:56.010 --> 00:13:57.920 align:middle line:84%
I'm running for vice
president to find

00:13:57.920 --> 00:14:00.350 align:middle line:90%
out what works in America.

00:14:00.350 --> 00:14:05.030 align:middle line:84%
And I got over 200 delegates,
more than anybody else,

00:14:05.030 --> 00:14:09.600 align:middle line:84%
except Geraldine Ferraro, and I
was the other woman nominated.

00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:13.260 align:middle line:84%
And I want to say the importance
here is if you have a vision,

00:14:13.260 --> 00:14:15.610 align:middle line:84%
like I had a vision
that our crisis is

00:14:15.610 --> 00:14:17.360 align:middle line:90%
the birth of something new.

00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:21.320 align:middle line:84%
And I stayed with it every
step of the way, whether it be

00:14:21.320 --> 00:14:23.560 align:middle line:84%
the NASA rockets or
running for vice president

00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:28.820 align:middle line:84%
or what I'm doing now, I ask
all visionaries, stay with it.

00:14:28.820 --> 00:14:29.540 align:middle line:90%
And do the work.

00:14:29.540 --> 00:14:31.470 align:middle line:90%
I mean, you got into the field.

00:14:31.470 --> 00:14:33.200 align:middle line:90%
You explored.

00:14:33.200 --> 00:14:34.430 align:middle line:90%
You asked the questions.

00:14:34.430 --> 00:14:37.000 align:middle line:90%
You were ferociously curious.

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:38.074 align:middle line:90%
You don't stop.

00:14:38.074 --> 00:14:39.240 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD:
I don't stop.

00:14:39.240 --> 00:14:44.000 align:middle line:84%
And it's amazing that you
demonstrate the reality of what

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:45.290 align:middle line:90%
your vision.

00:14:45.290 --> 00:14:48.680 align:middle line:84%
And this goes back to
conscious evolution.

00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:52.950 align:middle line:90%
You and I are evolution.

00:14:52.950 --> 00:14:55.900 align:middle line:90%
We are the universe in person.

00:14:55.900 --> 00:14:57.580 align:middle line:84%
That give me chills
when you say that.

00:14:57.580 --> 00:15:03.210 align:middle line:84%
The universe always wants
more consciousness, more life.

00:15:03.210 --> 00:15:05.980 align:middle line:84%
You can see from the billions
of years of evolution.

00:15:05.980 --> 00:15:09.042 align:middle line:84%
So when you and I or
any of the listeners

00:15:09.042 --> 00:15:12.690 align:middle line:84%
want more expression
of their own vision,

00:15:12.690 --> 00:15:15.380 align:middle line:90%
that's the universe wanting it.

00:15:15.380 --> 00:15:18.750 align:middle line:84%
It's not just your own
little private story.

00:15:18.750 --> 00:15:23.280 align:middle line:84%
We have footage of the speech
that Barbara gave at the 1984

00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:24.980 align:middle line:90%
Democratic National Convention.

00:15:24.980 --> 00:15:27.320 align:middle line:84%
It is a very similar
story to today.

00:15:27.320 --> 00:15:28.020 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

