00:27:01.883 --> 00:27:15.540 align:middle line:90%


00:27:15.540 --> 00:27:17.020 align:middle line:84%
Welcome back to
"Gaiam Inspirations."

00:27:17.020 --> 00:27:17.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:27:17.730 --> 00:27:20.810 align:middle line:84%
And my guest is visionary
futurist Barbara Marx Hubbard.

00:27:20.810 --> 00:27:23.500 align:middle line:84%
And we're talking about
creating a new worldview

00:27:23.500 --> 00:27:25.280 align:middle line:90%
of conscious evolution.

00:27:25.280 --> 00:27:28.230 align:middle line:84%
One of the things I'm really
sensitive to is making sure

00:27:28.230 --> 00:27:30.980 align:middle line:84%
that this conversation
applies to everyone,

00:27:30.980 --> 00:27:34.580 align:middle line:84%
is a practical conversation,
and as big and as large

00:27:34.580 --> 00:27:36.200 align:middle line:84%
as the conversation
can be, and is

00:27:36.200 --> 00:27:40.046 align:middle line:84%
necessary about
conscious evolution and

00:27:40.046 --> 00:27:42.720 align:middle line:90%
our whole evolutionary story.

00:27:42.720 --> 00:27:45.120 align:middle line:84%
I want to find out how it
relates to people when they're

00:27:45.120 --> 00:27:47.240 align:middle line:84%
hitting massive
depression or where

00:27:47.240 --> 00:27:52.190 align:middle line:84%
they're lost about a purpose in
life or financial devastation.

00:27:52.190 --> 00:27:53.280 align:middle line:90%
How does that apply?

00:27:53.280 --> 00:27:54.780 align:middle line:10%
Well, I just like
to tell you what

00:27:54.780 --> 00:27:58.630 align:middle line:10%
happened to me, because
when I had up to about

00:27:58.630 --> 00:28:01.610 align:middle line:10%
my fourth child, I was OK.

00:28:01.610 --> 00:28:02.870 align:middle line:10%
This is 1951.

00:28:02.870 --> 00:28:05.660 align:middle line:10%
And it was the era of the
woman who you get married,

00:28:05.660 --> 00:28:08.470 align:middle line:10%
you have babies, you take care
of your house and your husband.

00:28:08.470 --> 00:28:12.180 align:middle line:10%
And I did it with great
joy, actually, until I

00:28:12.180 --> 00:28:14.200 align:middle line:10%
started to get depressed.

00:28:14.200 --> 00:28:16.670 align:middle line:84%
And at that time,
in the late '50s,

00:28:16.670 --> 00:28:19.180 align:middle line:84%
the depression was
considered neurotic.

00:28:19.180 --> 00:28:21.650 align:middle line:90%
And I went to a psychiatrist.

00:28:21.650 --> 00:28:23.870 align:middle line:84%
He said, well, you're
obviously what's wrong.

00:28:23.870 --> 00:28:25.490 align:middle line:90%
Then I read Betty Friedan.

00:28:25.490 --> 00:28:28.200 align:middle line:84%
And I found out that
thousands of women

00:28:28.200 --> 00:28:29.950 align:middle line:90%
had something-- what was it?

00:28:29.950 --> 00:28:32.910 align:middle line:90%
It was a loss of identity.

00:28:32.910 --> 00:28:34.500 align:middle line:90%
Yes, we were wife and mother.

00:28:34.500 --> 00:28:36.170 align:middle line:90%
But there was more.

00:28:36.170 --> 00:28:38.200 align:middle line:90%
And then I read Abraham Maslow.

00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:41.200 align:middle line:84%
And he said, every
joyful, creative person

00:28:41.200 --> 00:28:44.030 align:middle line:84%
has one thing in
common-- something

00:28:44.030 --> 00:28:48.650 align:middle line:84%
that they feel called to do,
life purpose, chosen vocation.

00:28:48.650 --> 00:28:53.930 align:middle line:84%
That when they do it, they're
self-rewarded and of service.

00:28:53.930 --> 00:28:57.450 align:middle line:84%
And so I began to look
for a life purpose

00:28:57.450 --> 00:28:59.830 align:middle line:90%
that would include my children.

00:28:59.830 --> 00:29:02.360 align:middle line:90%
But I was only 29 or 30.

00:29:02.360 --> 00:29:06.360 align:middle line:84%
Instead of being at the
end, I was at the beginning.

00:29:06.360 --> 00:29:12.320 align:middle line:84%
And so I took the depression
as a signaled something more

00:29:12.320 --> 00:29:13.877 align:middle line:90%
to be expressed.

00:29:13.877 --> 00:29:15.010 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: So where
did you start?

00:29:15.010 --> 00:29:17.260 align:middle line:84%
Where did you start looking
for that bigger conversation?

00:29:17.260 --> 00:29:18.560 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX HUBBARD:
I started to look

00:29:18.560 --> 00:29:21.610 align:middle line:84%
because of a reading
Abraham Maslow--

00:29:21.610 --> 00:29:24.300 align:middle line:90%
anything that attracted me.

00:29:24.300 --> 00:29:27.600 align:middle line:84%
And so I began to
do in my reading,

00:29:27.600 --> 00:29:31.650 align:middle line:84%
I was attracted to,
actually, Abraham Maslow.

00:29:31.650 --> 00:29:33.560 align:middle line:84%
And so what I did
is I called him

00:29:33.560 --> 00:29:35.340 align:middle line:90%
up and invited him for lunch.

00:29:35.340 --> 00:29:36.260 align:middle line:90%
Himself?

00:29:36.260 --> 00:29:37.010 align:middle line:90%
Himself.

00:29:37.010 --> 00:29:39.650 align:middle line:84%
What's the hierarchy
of needs mean?

00:29:39.650 --> 00:29:40.720 align:middle line:90%
My goodness.

00:29:40.720 --> 00:29:41.860 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:29:41.860 --> 00:29:44.210 align:middle line:90%
See this is what-- I was bold.

00:29:44.210 --> 00:29:49.770 align:middle line:84%
So when you get this depression,
you have to ask yourself,

00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:53.100 align:middle line:84%
what glimmer of
something attracts you?

00:29:53.100 --> 00:29:54.490 align:middle line:90%
It could be an organization.

00:29:54.490 --> 00:29:55.410 align:middle line:90%
It could be a book.

00:29:55.410 --> 00:29:57.930 align:middle line:84%
It could be some
kind of activity.

00:29:57.930 --> 00:30:00.260 align:middle line:90%
You start to move toward it.

00:30:00.260 --> 00:30:02.470 align:middle line:90%
And that takes courage.

00:30:02.470 --> 00:30:05.320 align:middle line:84%
LISA GARR: What did
Abraham Maslow say to you?

00:30:05.320 --> 00:30:06.730 align:middle line:84%
BARBARA MARX
HUBBARD: He said yes.

00:30:06.730 --> 00:30:07.610 align:middle line:90%
He said yes.

00:30:07.610 --> 00:30:10.990 align:middle line:84%
I said, you have saved
my life, because I

00:30:10.990 --> 00:30:12.980 align:middle line:90%
realized I'm not neurotic.

00:30:12.980 --> 00:30:16.030 align:middle line:90%
I'm just an under expressed.

00:30:16.030 --> 00:30:19.520 align:middle line:84%
So we had lunch
together in New York.

00:30:19.520 --> 00:30:22.180 align:middle line:90%
And I told him all my problems.

00:30:22.180 --> 00:30:27.220 align:middle line:84%
And he said, no, Barbara,
you represent life.

00:30:27.220 --> 00:30:31.840 align:middle line:84%
I will give you the names
of 300 people I've collected

00:30:31.840 --> 00:30:35.440 align:middle line:84%
over the years-- all of whom
he called the good souls,

00:30:35.440 --> 00:30:37.460 align:middle line:90%
you psychic.

00:30:37.460 --> 00:30:39.890 align:middle line:84%
This is what happens
if you say yes.

00:30:39.890 --> 00:30:45.240 align:middle line:84%
I then decided to write
a letter to 300 people.

00:30:45.240 --> 00:30:47.760 align:middle line:84%
My question was, what do
you think is the next step

00:30:47.760 --> 00:30:49.830 align:middle line:90%
for the future good?

00:30:49.830 --> 00:30:53.660 align:middle line:84%
So after Maslow
gave me these names,

00:30:53.660 --> 00:30:55.160 align:middle line:90%
I wrote a letter to them.

00:30:55.160 --> 00:30:58.760 align:middle line:84%
What do you think is the next
step for the future good?

00:30:58.760 --> 00:31:03.912 align:middle line:84%
People like Thomas Merton
and Jonas Salk and others.

00:31:03.912 --> 00:31:06.290 align:middle line:90%
And some of the wrote back.

00:31:06.290 --> 00:31:09.140 align:middle line:90%
And I then called them up.

00:31:09.140 --> 00:31:14.480 align:middle line:84%
So my path was to take
depression as a signal

00:31:14.480 --> 00:31:16.590 align:middle line:90%
and look for life purpose.

00:31:16.590 --> 00:31:21.730 align:middle line:84%
And I think as you get
beyond your very early years,

00:31:21.730 --> 00:31:25.260 align:middle line:84%
the discovery of
